Take it after fasting overnight with a large glass of tap water at least half an hour before any food, drink or other medication. You must also remain upright or standing for this half hour. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.AlendronateRisedronate is to be taken once a week. Take it after fasting overnight with a large glass of tap water at least half an hour before any food, drink or other medication. You must also remain upright or standing for this half hour. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.RisedronateIbandronate is to be taken once a month. Take it after fasting overnight with a large glass of tap water at least half an hour before any food, drink or other medication. You must also remain upright or standing for this half hour. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.IbandronateThis medication is taken daily. Take it with water in the evening at least 2 hours after any food and drink other than water and then remain fasted for the next 2 hours. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.StrontiumThis is a once a year injection. We will arrange an appointment for you at the Rheumatology Day Unit for this. We need to ensure your Vitamin D levels are adequate before your infusion, and may need to send you some medication to help this which may slightly delay your treatment. If you have not had an appointment arranged within one month please contact us on 01865 227647 to discuss this further.ZoledronateThis is an injection every six months. The first injection will be given at the hospital and the rest of the injections arranged by your GP. We need to ensure your Vitamin D levels are adequate before the injection, so may need to send you some medication to treat this which may slightly delay your treatment. We will contact you to arrange an appointment to have your injection. Please ring 01865 227647 if you have any questions.DenosumabThis is a daily injection which you will be taught to give yourself. We have to make a special application to the Primary Care Trust for them to agree to fund the treatment. This means there will be a delay but we will contact you when we have further information. Please ring 01865 227647 If you have any questions.Teriparatide

gppatientadvicetextPatient Advice GP Letter-enumeratedDirectorystringOptional-Good dental hygiene is recommended with this treatment, and the dentist should be informed at the next routine visit.
If you have unexplained new pain in the thigh or in your groin whilst taking osteoporosis drug treatments for more than a year it would be sensible to discuss this with your doctor or other health professional as soon as practical. GeneralAlendronate is to be taken once a week. Take it after fasting overnight with a large glass of tap water at least half an hour before any food, drink or other medication. You must also remain upright or standing for this half hour. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.AlendronateRisedronate is to be taken once a week. Take it after fasting overnight with a large glass of tap water at least half an hour before any food, drink or other medication. You must also remain upright or standing for this half hour. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.RisedronateIbandronate is to be taken once a month. Take it after fasting overnight with a large glass of tap water at least half an hour before any food, drink or other medication. You must also remain upright or standing for this half hour. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.IbandronateThis medication is taken daily. Take it with water in the evening at least 2 hours after any food and drink other than water and then remain fasted for the next 2 hours. Please read the information leaflet carefully as it is important you follow the instructions exactly to get benefit from your treatment.StrontiumThis is a once a year injection. We will arrange an appointment for you at the Rheumatology Day Unit for this. We need to ensure your Vitamin D levels are adequate before your infusion, and may need to send you some medication to help this which may slightly delay your treatment. If you have not had an appointment arranged within one month please contact us on 01865 227647 to discuss this further.ZoledronateThis is an injection every six months. The first injection will be given at the hospital and the rest of the injections arranged by your GP. We need to ensure your Vitamin D levels are adequate before the injection, so may need to send you some medication to treat this which may slightly delay your treatment. We will contact you to arrange an appointment to have your injection. Please ring 01865 227647 if you have any questions.DenosumabThis is a daily injection which you will be taught to give yourself. We have to make a special application to the Primary Care Trust for them to agree to fund the treatment. This means there will be a delay but we will contact you when we have further information. Please ring 01865 227647 If you have any questions.Teriparatide
